<br />

<br />

<br />
Offensive Results: (KillTime = time in seconds to kill 10mobs, all other figures are DPS) 
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Code:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="code">Pet&nbsp; &nbsp;KillTime&nbsp; &nbsp;Melee&nbsp; &nbsp;Spell&nbsp; &nbsp;DS&nbsp; &nbsp;Total&nbsp; &nbsp;NonDS 
<br />
Epic&nbsp; &nbsp; 1050&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;61.2&nbsp; &nbsp; 38.6&nbsp; &nbsp;20.3&nbsp; 120.1&nbsp; &nbsp; 99.8 
<br />
Air&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;1275&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;79.1&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;7.1&nbsp; &nbsp;12.7&nbsp; &nbsp;98.9&nbsp; &nbsp; 86.2 
<br />
Water&nbsp; &nbsp;1048&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;78.3&nbsp; &nbsp; 21.6&nbsp; &nbsp;20.4&nbsp; 120.3&nbsp; &nbsp; 99.9
<br />
Earth&nbsp; &nbsp;1185&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;73.8&nbsp; &nbsp; 11.1&nbsp; &nbsp;21.5&nbsp; 106.4&nbsp; &nbsp; 84.9
<br />
Fire&nbsp; &nbsp; 1172&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;35.8&nbsp; &nbsp; 50.5&nbsp; &nbsp;21.3&nbsp; 107.6&nbsp; &nbsp; 86.3
<br />
Air&#40;G&#41;&nbsp; 1350&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;72.5&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;7.9&nbsp; &nbsp;13.0&nbsp; &nbsp;93.4&nbsp; &nbsp; 80.4
<br />
MS4&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;1174&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;86.4&nbsp; &nbsp; 10.9&nbsp; &nbsp;12.1&nbsp; 107.4&nbsp; &nbsp; 97.3
<br />
Air&#40;RS&#41; 1254&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;79.7&nbsp; &nbsp; 12.3&nbsp; &nbsp; 8.5&nbsp; 100.5&nbsp; &nbsp; 88.2
<br />
MS4&#40;RS&#41; 1091&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;94.5&nbsp; &nbsp; 12.3&nbsp; &nbsp; 8.7&nbsp; 115.5&nbsp; &nbsp;103.2
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I think its clear that Air pet is the best tank pet we currently have (no idea on MS4) and is a fair amount better than Earth pet. Earth pet mitigates better but the lack of stun and the root stopping mobs running hurts it.
<br />

<br />
If a mob is stunnable and runs use Air, its stunnable but doesn't run I still suspect Air is better but if its not stunnable and doesn't run then Earth will be a better pet to use.
<br />

<br />
I included Fire but its really hard to gauge its performance as it runs oom so fast. It does cast manaskin so that reduces the dps taken slightly but to gain anything like comparable DPS out of it compared to any of the other pets you need to wait for it to be full mana so there is more downtime. It ran oom during everyfight and melee'd the mobs down at the end everytime. ALso what I noticed it doing without fail was when oom it would root the mob everytime it had regenned enough mana to cast root. This was usually after it snared the mob, which it did most times as it neared oom.
<br />

<br />
The spells it cast were
<br />

<br />
Lure of Frost
<br />
Thunderbold
<br />
Voltaic Draught
<br />
Draught of Fire
<br />
Ice Comet
<br />
Draught of Jiva
<br />
Elnerick Entombment of Ice
<br />
Atol's Spectral Shackles
<br />
Root
<br />

<br />
It buffed itself with Shield of the Magi, Manaskin and O'keills Flickering Flame. It seems to have around 2600 mana from quick checks of how much it cast. I don't think there is a use for Fire pet at all.
<br />

<br />
In conclusion (my opinion only)
<br />

<br />
Air is the best tank, Water is the highest DPS (equal to epic when tanking, will exceed epic from behind), Earth is situational in its use, Fire (and Epic in most situations) just suck.
<br />

<br />
I included a test of a GoDS focussed Air pet so people can compare it to the SoAS one.
<br />

<br />
I do think the foci should have a larger improvement on a pets DPS (I think its probably fine defensively now as there are noticeable differences).
<br />

<br />
My suggestions for PoP pets would be to make say GoDS foci = current SoAS, bump up DPoC to be midway between new GoDS and unfocussed, Minion of Eternity should be say 10% above what it is now (melee DPS), with Ritual Summoning 10% above that and the GoD foci a further 10% ahead.
<br />

<br />
I'd not make any changes to Epic as I think its clear that I wish that pet to die.
<br />

<br />
EDIT: Added MS4 data under the exact same conditions as used in the other tests. I think it can be seen that its basically an Air pet than does more damage.
<br />

<br />
EDIT: Added Ritual Summoning focussed data for Air and MS4 pets.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=342751" target="_blank" class="postlink">Kirium</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.cestusdei.org" target="_blank" class="postlink">Cestus Dei</a>
<br />
