			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The (G) did mean a GoDS summoned Ward of Xegony. I don't have DPoC as I had VT gloves and Time focus before it was added to the game so had no need to spend 760 pts on it. Epic pet was summoned with GoDS though so the Epic and Air pet did use the same focus for at least one comparison.
<br />

<br />
The mobs been fought were the Lvl 52 Blood Ravens in PoN. I find these excellent mobs to parse against as there is a place with 4 static spawns in PoN where it is convenient to parse without interference. Also the mobs always spawn at the same level with the same min/max hit, same HP as far as I can tell.
<br />

<br />
One thing that does seem pretty clear is that all pets (except Air) have the same avoidance ability). Air does appear to avoid damage better than the rest. This coupled with the stun makes him the superior tank pet even though Earth does mitigate damage better. Air is also the 2nd best aggro pet (afetr Epic) so you can nuke more using him than when using Earth. 
<br />

<br />
The Fire pet seemed to nearly chain cast 'useful' spells (the nukes/nuke+stun) until it got low on mana. Its DPS during this time was high, higher than any other pet I would say. The problem is it went oom so fast the mob was nowhere near dead when it stopped nuking. Fire pet seems to have little to no use at all as he goes oom to fast. Maybe reclaiming him once he is oom would work but I dunno as I can't easily test that solo. 
<br />

<br />
As for what I think the pets should be doing DPS wise if we take Air pet as been the standard then currently a SoAS Air pet will do high 80's (including spells/procs) when tanking a low blue con. This won't change much with mob level until it gets really high. If pet was attacking from rear it would gain 10 to 15% in melee damage bringing its DPS to 100'ish. I think this is what level a GoDS pet should be at. SoAS would be 10% higher so around 110, RS around 121 and Minion of Discord pet around 133 dps. DPoC I would put midway between GoDS and unfocussed (no idea what unfocussed pet would do).
<br />

<br />
Water/Earth etc would scale in a similar fashion. Water does considerably more than Air when attacking from behind gaining around 15-20 dps melee + more spells/procs when they land. So a GoDS water pet from behind should be doing 130'ish dps compared to Air pets 100. The other foci would scale in a similiar fashion. This would put Time focussed Water pet doing upward of 140dps when its spells land.
<br />

<br />
I wish I had MS4 to run the same tests on but it still eludes me despite many, many hours spent killing Chavoor.
<br />

<br />
Edit: Also I think they need to add Minion of Darkness (VT focus) to 1 or 2 more items in PoP/GoD. Say add something in Tier 3 and maybe an augment say with the focus on in Sewers/Vxed off one of the nameds.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=342751" target="_blank" class="postlink">Kirium</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.cestusdei.org" target="_blank" class="postlink">Cestus Dei</a>
<br />
Veeshan</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
