			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I think everyone is talking from the same hymn book with respect to pets now.
<br />

<br />

<br />
 One of the things I liked about my mage was his variety of pets. Soon after PoP, 90% of mages were using WoX or Epic. A few liked to use SoM for the DPS (and assassinating when farming  :twisted: )
<br />

<br />
Recently Sony have managed to increase the ability to vary which pet we choose, and I think some more pushing should happen with regard to this.
<br />

<br />

<br />
 Eandori and Kirium's suggestions re. pet DPS is pretty much in the right ballpark I think. Enough to be noticeable, but not enough to threaten melee PCs without the addition of our nukeage.
<br />

<br />
On 60-65 mobs, 100dps from Air (without DS), 125dps from Water (from behind), 90dps from Earth (lower DPS to offset  20% increase in HPs over air) seems about right for a DPoC focussed pet.
<br />

<br />

<br />
 Fire pet suffers because of his style at present .. if the devs increase his nuke DPS hugely, he will be imbalanced when cast/reclaimed. I reckon he should melee dps a little better, nuke less frequently and put out maybe 135dps over a 4-5minute fight. His HPs and mitigation should stink badly so he doesn't make water redundant.
<br />

<br />

<br />
 Focus items past DPoC should add about 5-10% each so they are noticeable but not sickeningly potent.
<br />

<br />

<br />
 My take on pet usage is:-
<br />

<br />
-<span style="font-weight: bold">Earth</span>- Pure meatshield with fair DPS/replacement MT for non-bossmob encounters or soloing nasty mobs.
<br />
-<span style="font-weight: bold">Air</span>- Good DPS, defensively good pet/good for grouping or soloing
<br />
-<span style="font-weight: bold">Water</span>- Very good DPS, requires some skill to use to full effect.
<br />
-<span style="font-weight: bold">Fire</span>- Pimp DPS but useless tanking ability(similar to level 49 pet with a wider range of spells)
<br />

<br />
Each pet has a little overlap next to its most similar neighbour.
<br />

<br />
 
<br />
 At the end of the day Ryan and his team will decide where pets go with respect to their damage output, not ourselves, but I think these suggestions and those from other mages are reasonable and would satisfy most of us.<br />_________________<br />-- I used to be an atheist until I became an Arch Convoker ~ <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=535614" target="_blank" class="postlink">Ducalio "Fivehead" Jeebus</a>--</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
