			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The other situation where Earth>Air is on mobs resistant to airpet stun, Ailees - (eg. very high end mobs, and most boss encounters). In these circumstance, Earth pets extra 20% hps outweighs the additional defensive ability of Air.
<br />

<br />
Prior to the mitigation changes, Air was far and away the best tank (with respect to mitigation) pet in almost any circumstance ... Earth is now definitely more useful than it used to be.
<br />

<br />
For soloing (except when reclaiming) Air is normally superior through its higher aggro, allowing you to nuke harder and therefore finish mobs quicker.
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">ps</span>.
<br />

<br />
I did a short series of logs earlier today in Chardok comparing Water and Air pets with DPoC focus, girdle, muzzle, 2 fists, elemental defender and full set of jewellry.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Mob</span>: Enslaved Iksar Miner, level 55, 9400hp (+/- 0.3%), fights to death every time.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Air Pet + DS tanking</span> - 90dps (avg. fight 104secs) - pet ended fight on 55-60%hps
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Water Pet + DS tanking</span> - 110dps (avg. fight 85secs) - pet ended fight on 35-40%hps
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Water Pet in backstab position </span>- 115dps (avg. fight 83secs)
<br />
(I basically stood getting beaten on by the mob while SoM poked from behind) - Ducalio ended fight on ~10%hps  <img src="images/smiles/icon_lol.gif" alt="Laughing out Loud" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
[<span style="font-weight: bold">Fire Pet in "backstab" position</span> - ~160dps until oom (after approx. 5k dd damage - I was too lazy to let pet "med" after self buffing so perhaps add another 1-1.5k nuke damage if allowed to get to full mana) then it tended to snare and/or root mob, and melee (I couldn't finish these kills as my 5khp were running too low waiting for pet to finish but melee was ~60dps :roll: )]
<br />

<br />
Didnt have too long to do much more than this, but it shows figures comparable to Kirium's parses on PoP mobs. I have little doubt that DPoC'd Epic would be able to at least match, and probably surpass Water pet dps tanking in this Kunark dungeon.
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline"><span style="font-weight: bold">edit</span>:</span> Assuming a negligible HP regen while in /attack, AIR took about 25dps (including stuns), WATER about 40dps, and DUCALIO about 50dps (960ac with vitue, max. defense/dodge[+8% mod]) .. might be worth sticking a decent tank in place of the mage (unarmed so no riposte damage) and seeing how pets compare with 'real' tanks ?<br />_________________<br />-- I used to be an atheist until I became an Arch Convoker ~ <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=535614" target="_blank" class="postlink">Ducalio "Fivehead" Jeebus</a>--</span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Ducalio on Sat Apr 24, 2004 10:39 am; edited 1 time in total</span></td>
