			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Very interesting results.  
<br />

<br />
I really would not have expected WoX and SoM to parse that high on a level 55 mob.  You verified the mobs HP several times with nukes and made sure his HP did not vary spawn to spawn right?  Best way for that is:
<br />

<br />
nuke for 1550 when he's full, write down his HP% after.  
<br />
Zone out, back in,  
<br />
nuke for 2k, write down his HP% after.  
<br />
Kill his ass, let him spawn again.
<br />
nuke for 1550 when he's full, write down his HP% after.  
<br />
Zone out, back in,  
<br />
nuke for 2k, write down his HP% after.  
<br />
Kill his ass, let him spawn again.
<br />
nuke for 1550 when he's full, write down his HP% after.  
<br />
Zone out, back in,  
<br />
nuke for 2k, write down his HP% after.  
<br />
Kill his ass, do some math.
<br />

<br />
-use this equation for each test result to determine HP, solve for X:  <span style="font-weight: bold">((nuke amount)*100)/(100-HP%) = X</span>
<br />
-if all the values for his HP agree, you have a good test mob <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" />  
<br />
-Be sure to use unfocused nukes, so the % damage done is consistent.  Makes it easier on you.
<br />

<br />
Yeah, you should try that same test with Epic pet.  See what he gets, as I believe he is our baseline for how the pets should be upgraded.  Gotta be sure to use mobs where his procs land well though, I'm curious how well his proc would land on that mob.<br />_________________<br /><Center><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=36994" target="_blank" class="postlink">Eandori (Retired)</a>
<br />
<span style="font-style: italic"><a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewtopic.php?t=13760" target="_blank" class="postlink">"The pinnacle of pet offensive power can be achieved at level 50 with the epic pet. Does this make sense?"</a></span>
<br />
</center></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
