				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Head down the "levi tunnel", past the area where the captain and BK are .. head all the way down and turn right at the bottom.
<br />

<br />
This is a little loop that has about 18 mobs including 2 name/PH spots.
<br />

<br />
Most pulls are 2 at a time, but a few are singles (more so once broken). Jobaber can easily handle 2 or 3 with just heals/nukes. As you have the root earring, it will be a piece of cake for you to rape this area Eandori (I used to go there with 10 insta-click root nets every night, and recharge them at the vendors afterwards .. pity that got nerfed  :evil: ).
<br />

<br />
My gut feeling is that Epic will be <span style="text-decoration: underline">very</span> effective here as the mobs have lowish resists ... Malosini may well improve his DPS, but I never bother as the PoP pets are 6-10 level higher than anything down there (except names who are also quite gimpy).
<br />

<br />
On a multi-pull Epic would likely struggle as he'd get beaten down faster ... but that's where root earring come in handy  :wink:
<br />

<br />
My advice is head down, and try out your pets .. the mitigation changes are very noticeable here.. I frequently have Job tanking 3 mobs simultaneously without any need to add TER to the heal mix.
<br />

<br />
Spawn timer is about 10 minutes for normal mobs, and 22 minutes for names/PH. If you go into the Herbalist area, pull with annul magic/pillage enchantment (<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=12900" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="font-weight: bold">NICE TOY!</span></a>) as many mobs will be shaman-buffed (haste+sow = bad  <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="icon_biggrin" border="0" /> ). Enjoy!
<br />

<br />
