			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">My method of determining a mobs HP's for pet dps calculations is different as I feel the nuke and note what percentage it drops to has too many inaccuracies due to the way EQ rounds percentages. Also mobs regen at a fair rate even when aggroed.
<br />

<br />
How I determined Blood Raven (and Nettling Wraiths) HP was as follows:
<br />

<br />
I used an Air pet with no DS and no proc weapons equipped so I could see every single point of damage done. I had to assume that the stun, if it lands always lands for full which is what the results of Ylaine's test 18months ago said.
<br />

<br />
To combat the mob regenning effect I ensured that when testing a mobs HP I killed the mob over roughly the same time as it would die when running the real tests (so 2 minutes in the case of Blood Ravens). 
<br />

<br />
I simply add up all the damage done via pet melee, nukes (I had to nuke to ensure mob died at right time) and the stun damage. Repeat a few times and see what you get.
<br />

<br />
The only inaccuracy is that the killing blow is always an 'overhit' so the mob will have less HP than the amount a parser says it took. However in the real tests this same effect will occur so it can be discounted.
<br />

<br />
Using this technique I determined Blood Ravens to have 12606 HP over a 2 min'ish fight.
<br />

<br />
I also did this for Nettling Wraiths in PoN (Lvl 55, always hit for 329) which I sometimes use as a higher level test subject. These mobs have 14543 HP again over 2min fights.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=342751" target="_blank" class="postlink">Kirium</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.cestusdei.org" target="_blank" class="postlink">Cestus Dei</a>
<br />
Veeshan</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
