			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Mob regen once aggro'ed in Chardok is either zero, or near zero. There were no instance using my technique of a calculated HP-range being outwith the area I suggested as the mob's "true" hit points.
<br />

<br />
When I used to use Wooly Spidersilk Nets to split pulls (100 seconds root with a 60dd component), the mobs would still be on 99%hps when I went back to get them maybe 60 seconds later.
<br />

<br />
Another test of this is to nuke the mob, then stand with it beating on you ... note the lack of mob regen here also.
<br />

<br />
In PoP, especially in PoStorms, I have seen plenty of problems with mobs getting "warp regen" on pulls, and agree with your HP analysis for your parses.
<br />

<br />
Even if there is a small discrepancy in calculated Hitpoints, the end result will be fairly similar, as we are looking at +/- 1% of mob total hitpoints (and therefore +/- 1% of parsed dps).<br />_________________<br />-- I used to be an atheist until I became an Arch Convoker ~ <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=535614" target="_blank" class="postlink">Ducalio "Fivehead" Jeebus</a>--</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
