				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I'd like to see someone do the dps of fire when chaining.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
I've done that.
<br />

<br />
Before he goes OOM, and if you engage him before he starts buffing, he will do between 130 and 180 DPS in nukes.  But shortly after he runs OOM and starts doing melee at a very small ~45 DPS.  It would seem that chain casting fire pets (new pet = full mana pool) would be a good tactic, but unfortunately you can't control what they do.  
<br />

<br />
Everytime I try that, I end up getting a few pets that pop out and start buffing themselves as soon as they are out.  So you must wait for the first buff to land, and dump their mana pool down a bit before the pet engages.
<br />

<br />
The other problem is that the Fire pet sometimes will run in and do lots of melee even when he has a mana pool left.  I tried it several times, and found the Fire pet to move between being pretty effective, to really lacking.
<br />

<br />
Great duel pet though.<br />_________________<br /><Center><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=36994" target="_blank" class="postlink">Eandori (Retired)</a>
